<PageLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="What cookies Admin's Choice uses, why, and how you can control them."
  updated="June 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Cookie Policy explains what cookies are, how Admin's Choice uses them,
    and how you can control them. It should be read alongside our
    <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What cookies are</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website.
    They are widely used to make sites work, to remember preferences, and to
    provide information to site owners and advertisers.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use cookies</h2>
  <p>The cookies on this site fall into a few categories:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Essential cookies.</strong> Needed for the site to function and to
      remember basic preferences such as light or dark mode. These cannot
      meaningfully be switched off and do not require consent.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Analytics cookies.</strong> Help us understand how visitors use the
      site so we can improve it. These collect information in aggregate and are
      treated as non-essential.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Advertising cookies.</strong> This site displays ads provided by
      one or more third-party advertising networks (currently including Google
      AdSense, and potentially others in future). These vendors and their
      partners set cookies to serve and measure ads. Where Google is used, its
      advertising cookies (including the DoubleClick cookie) may show ads based
      on your visits to this and other sites. These are non-essential.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Affiliate cookies.</strong> Some pages link to third-party
      retailers and affiliate programs (currently including Amazon Associates,
      and potentially others). If you follow an affiliate link, the destination
      site may set its own cookies to attribute the referral. These are set by
      the third party under its own policy.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Consent (EEA, UK, and Switzerland)</h2>
  <p>
    If you visit from the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or
    Switzerland, non-essential cookies — analytics and advertising — are
    <strong>not stored until you give consent</strong>. On your first visit, a
    consent banner lets you accept or reject these cookies. You can change or
    withdraw your choice at any time using the <strong>privacy settings</strong>
    link in the footer of every page. Consent is managed through a
    Google-certified Consent Management Platform supporting the IAB Transparency
    &amp; Consent Framework. If you decline, advertising vendors that support it
    serve only non-personalised ads, and advertising cookies are limited to
    frequency capping, aggregated reporting, and fraud prevention.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Some cookies are set by third parties, such as advertising and analytics
    providers. These are governed by those third parties' own policies. You can
    learn more and opt out of personalised advertising at
    <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>,
    <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info</a>,
    or
    <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">youronlinechoices.eu</a>
    (EU).
  </p>

  <h2>Controlling cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Beyond the consent banner, most browsers let you view, manage, and delete
    cookies through their settings, and block cookies from some or all sites.
    Blocking essential cookies may affect how parts of the site work. For
    guidance, see your browser's help pages.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Cookie Policy as our use of cookies changes. The "Last
    updated" date above reflects the most recent revision.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
